2 Section 3. Section 76-6-104, MCA, is amended to read:
3 "76-6-104. Definitions. The following terms whenever used or referred to in this chapter shall have
4 the following meanings unless a different meaning is clearly indicated by the context:
5 (1) "Comprehensive planning" means planning for development and shall include includes:
6 (a) preparation of general physical plans with respect to the pattern and intensity of land use and
7 the provision of public facilities, including transportation facilities, together with long-range fiscal plans for such
8 the development as a guide for long-range development;
9 (b) programming and financing plans for capital improvements;
10 (c) coordination of all related plans and planned activities at both the intragovernmental and
11 intergovernmental levels; and
12 (d) preparation of regulatory and administrative measures in support of the foregoing subsections
13 (1)(a) through (1)(c).
14 (2) "Conservation easement" means an easement or restriction for a term of years but not in
15 perpetuity, running with the land and assignable, whereby through which an owner of land voluntarily
16 relinquishes to the holder of such the easement or restriction any or all rights to construct improvements upon
17 on the land or to substantially alter the natural character of the land or to permit the construction of
18 improvements upon on the land or the substantial alteration of the natural character of the land, except as this
19 right is expressly reserved in the instruments evidencing the easement or restriction.
20 (3) "Open-space land" means any land which that is provided or preserved for:
21 (a) park or recreational purposes;
22 (b) conservation of land or other natural resources;
23 (c) historic or scenic purposes; or
24 (d) assisting in the shaping of the character, direction, and timing of community development.
25 (4) "Public body" means the state, counties, cities, towns, and other municipalities.
26 (5) "Qualified private organization" means a private organization:
27 (a) competent to own interests in real property;
28 (b) which that qualifies and holds a general tax exemption under the federal Internal Revenue
