8 Section 4. Section 76-6-202, MCA, is amended to read:
9 "76-6-202. Duration of conservation easements. Conservation easements may be granted either in
10 perpetuity or for a term of not less than 15 years and no more than 40 years. If granted for a term of years, that
11 term may not be less than 15 years. An easement granted for a term of years may be renewed for a term of 15
12 or more years upon a new term through the execution of a new granting instrument by the parties, except that
13 the easement may not be in effect for more than 40 years."
14
15 Section 5. Section 76-6-203, MCA, is amended to read:
16 "76-6-203. Types of permissible easements. Easements Except as provided in [section 1],
17 easements or restrictions under this chapter may prohibit or limit any or all of the following:
18 (1) structures--construction or placing of buildings, camping trailers, housetrailers, mobile homes,
19 roads, signs, billboards or other advertising, utilities, or other structures on or above the ground;
20 (2) landfill--dumping or placing of soil or other substance or material as landfill or dumping or
21 placing of trash, waste, or unsightly or offensive materials;
22 (3) vegetation--removal or destruction of trees, shrubs, or other vegetation;
23 (4) loam, gravel, etc. and similar materials--excavation, dredging, or removal of loam, peat, gravel,
24 soil, rock, or other material substance;
25 (5) surface use--surface use except for such the purposes of permitting the land or water area to
26 remain predominantly in its existing condition;
27 (6) acts detrimental to conservation--activities detrimental to drainage, flood control, water
28 conservation, erosion control, soil conservation, or fish and wildlife habitat and preservation;
